The global e-scooter/moped and e-motorcycle market can be segmented based on product type, battery type, voltage, and end-user. In terms of product type, the market is categorized into e-scooter, e-moped, and e-motorcycle. Battery type segmentation includes lead acid and lithium ion batteries, which have different performance characteristics and costs. The voltage segment comprises various options such as 36V, 48V, 60V, and 72V, each offering different power outputs and range capabilities. Lastly, the end-user segment differentiates between residential and commercial users, each with distinct needs and usage patterns.

